This paper discusses the techniques used by Indian ISPs to censor websites, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also investigates the consistency of website blocklists across ISPs, which could be considered a topic in computer networks (cs.NI) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of SNI inspection for blocking websites is a topic in computer systems and hardware (cs.AR) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the compilation of a list of potentially blocked websites, which could be considered a topic in cybercrime (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a suite of tests for detecting censorship, which could be considered a topic in cybersecurity (cs.CR) or computer systems and hardware (cs.AR).
